Stunning Fist			TYPE:General.Fighter.AttackOption													PREFEAT:1,Improved Unarmed Strike									PREMULT:1,[PREATT:8],[PREVARGTEQ:BaseAttackBonus,8],[PRECLASS:1,Monk=1]																																																															PRESTAT:2,DEX=13,WIS=13							DEFINE:StunningFistMonkLVL|0	DEFINE:StunningFistAttack|0	DEFINE:StunningFistDC|10+WIS	DESC:You know how to strike opponents in vulnerable areas.	BENEFIT:%1/day you may stun an opponant with a carefully placed unarmed attack (DC %2)|StunningFistAttack|StunningFistDC																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																													BONUS:VAR|StunningFistDC|TL/2|TYPE=NoStack	BONUS:VAR|StunningFistAttack|StunningFistMonkLVL+(TL-StunningFistMonkLVL)/4|TYPE=NoStack												SOURCEPAGE:p.101	SOURCESHORT:PH
Toughness				TYPE:General																																																																											DESC:You are tougher than normal.	BENEFIT:You gain +3 hit points.																																																																																																																																																																																																												STACK:YES	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NOCHOICE																																																																																																		BONUS:HP|CURRENTMAX|3																																																							SOURCEPAGE:p.101	SOURCESHORT:PH
Tower Shield Proficiency	TYPE:General																														PREMULT:1,[PREPROFWITHSHIELD:3,TYPE.Buckler,TYPE.Light,TYPE.Heavy],[PREFEAT:1,Shield Proficiency]																													DESC:You are proficient with tower shields.	BENEFIT:You can use a tower shield and suffer only the standard penalties.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																									AUTO:SHIELDPROF|SHIELDTYPE=Tower																																																																																																																									SOURCEPAGE:p.101	SOURCESHORT:PH
Track					TYPE:General																																																																											DESC:You can follow the trails of creatures and characters across most types of terrain.	BENEFIT:To find tracks or to follow them for 1 mile requires a successful Survival check. You must make another Survival check every time the tracks become difficult to follow.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.101	SOURCESHORT:PH
Trample				TYPE:General.Fighter.AttackOption													PREFEAT:1,Mounted Combat																											PRESKILL:1,Ride=1																										DESC:You are trained in using your mount to knock down opponents.	BENEFIT:When you attempt to overrun an opponent while mounted, your target may not choose to avoid you. Your mount may make one hoof attack against any target you knock down.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																						SOURCEPAGE:p.101	SOURCESHORT:PH
Two-Weapon Defense		TYPE:General.Fighter.ModifyAC														PREFEAT:1,Two-Weapon Fighting																														PRESTAT:1,DEX=15								DEFINE:TwoWeaponShield|0											DESC:Your two-weapon fighting style bolsters your defense as well as your offense.	BENEFIT:When wielding a double weapon or two weapons (not including natural weapons or unarmed strikes), you gain a +1 shield bonus to your AC. When you are fighting defensively or using the total defense action, this shield bonus increases to +2.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																															BONUS:COMBAT|AC|TwoWeaponShield|TYPE=Shield|PREMULT:1,[PREEQUIP:1,TYPE=Double],[PREMULT:2,[PREEQUIPPRIMARY:1,TYPE=Melee],[PREEQUIPSECONDARY:1,TYPE=Melee]]																																BONUS:VAR|TwoWeaponShield|1																														SOURCEPAGE:p.102	SOURCESHORT:PH
Two-Weapon Fighting		TYPE:General.Fighter																																																	PRESTAT:1,DEX=15																							DESC:You can fight with a weapon in each hand. You can make one extra attack each round with the second weapon.	BENEFIT:You can fight with a weapon in each hand. You can make one extra attack each round with the second weapon.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																					BONUS:COMBAT|TOHIT-PRIMARY|2	BONUS:COMBAT|TOHIT-SECONDARY|6																																																																																	SOURCEPAGE:p.102	SOURCESHORT:PH
Weapon Finesse			TYPE:General.Fighter																													PREMULT:1,[PREATT:1],[PREVARGTEQ:BaseAttackBonus,1]																																					DESC:You are especially skilled at using weapons that can benefit as much from Dexterity as from Strength.	BENEFIT:With a light weapon, rapier, whip, or spiked chain made for a creature of your size category, you may use your Dexterity modifier instead of your Strength modifier on attack rolls. If you carry a shield, its armor check penalty applies to your attack rolls.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																												BONUS:COMBAT|TOHIT.Finesseable|(max(STR,DEX+SHIELDACCHECK)-STR)|TYPE=NotRanged																																																																														SOURCEPAGE:p.102	SOURCESHORT:PH
Weapon Focus			TYPE:General.Fighter																													PREMULT:1,[PREATT:1],[PREVARGTEQ:BaseAttackBonus,1]																																					DESC:Choose one type of weapon, such as greataxe. You can also choose unarmed strike or grapple (or ray, if you are a spellcaster) as your weapon for purposes of this feat. You are especially good at using this weapon. (If you have chosen ray, you are especially good with rays, such as the one produced by the ray of frost spell.)	BENEFIT:You gain a +1 bonus on all attack rolls you make using the selected weapon.																																																																																																																																																																																																					MULT:YES	CHOOSE:WEAPONPROFICIENCY|PC																																																																																																																																															BONUS:WEAPONPROF=%LIST|TOHIT|1						SOURCEPAGE:p.102	SOURCESHORT:PH
Weapon Specialization		TYPE:Special.Fighter															PREFEAT:1,Weapon Focus																																			PREVARGTEQ:WeapSpecQualify,1																	DESC:Choose one type of weapon, such as greataxe, for which you have already selected the Weapon Focus feat. You can also choose unarmed strike or grapple as your weapon for purposes of this feat. You deal extra damage when using this weapon.	BENEFIT:You gain a +2 bonus on all damage rolls you make using the selected weapon.																																																																																																																																																																																																					MULT:YES	CHOOSE:WEAPONPROFICIENCY|FEAT=Weapon Focus																																																																																																																																												BONUS:WEAPONPROF=%LIST|DAMAGE|2						SOURCEPAGE:p.102	SOURCESHORT:PH
Whirlwind Attack			TYPE:General.Fighter.AttackOption													PREFEAT:4,Dodge,Mobility,Spring Attack,Combat Expertise					PREMULT:1,[PREATT:4],[PREVARGTEQ:BaseAttackBonus,4]												PRESTAT:2,DEX=13,INT=13																						DESC:You can strike nearby opponents in an amazing, spinning attack.	BENEFIT:When you use the full attack action, you can give up your regular attacks and instead make one melee attack at your full base attack bonus against each opponent within reach.																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																																					SOURCEPAGE:p.102	SOURCESHORT:PH
Widen Spell				TYPE:Metamagic.Wizard																																																																										DESC:You can increase the area of your spells.	BENEFIT:You can alter a burst, emanation, line, or spread shaped spell to increase its area. Any numeric measurements of the spell's area increase by 100%%. A widened spell uses up a spell slot three levels higher than the spell's actual level. Spells that do not have an area of one of these four sorts are not affected by this feat.																																																																																																																																																																																																																								ADDSPELLLEVEL:3																																																																																																	SOURCEPAGE:p.102	SOURCESHORT:PH

